						<div class="postbody"><em>(opens GIMP and measures key points)</em>
<br />It is being stretched. It looks like just over 254.5 horizontal pixels of the 256 are being displayed, stretching distances and triggering your video card's linear interpolation. The distance from the top of the M in MARIO to the top of the cracked blocks is also slightly greater than it should be: 193 pixels instead of the expected 192. Try loading up a ROM that just displays a grid so that you can use it for calibration.</div>

